New Environment
-----------------------
MS .net 3.51
VMWARE Player 12
Linux Mint 17.2

follow process below for adding 30GB /dev/sdb and creating datavg

idisk -l shows as sdc

pvcreate /dev/sdc
vgcreate datavg /dev/sdc
lvcreate -l 100%FREE -n lvol1 datavg 
mkdir /data
mkfs.ext4 /dev/datavg/lvol1
tune2fs -c 0 /dev/datavg/lvol1
tune2fs -i 0 /dev/datavg/lvol1
mount /dev/datavg/lvol1 /data
mkdir /data/josh
chown josh:josh /data/josh
vi /etc/fstab
shutdown -r now

#sudo apt-get -y install open-vm-tools
install vmware tools

apt-get -y install lib32stdc++6 lib32z1

http://developer.android.com/sdk/index.html
https://dl.google.com/dl/android/studio/ide-zips/1.3.2.0/android-studio-ide-141.2178183-linux.zip

http://developer.android.com/ndk/downloads/index.html
http://dl.google.com/android/ndk/android-ndk-r10e-linux-x86_64.bin

http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk8-downloads-2133151.html
http://download.oracle.com/otn-pub/java/jdk/8u60-b27/jdk-8u60-linux-x64.tar.gz


mv Downloads/jdk-8u60-linux-x64.tar.gz .
tar zxf jdk-8u60-linux-x64.tar.gz


mv Downloads/android-studio-ide-141.2178183-linux.zip .
 unzip android-studio-ide-141.2178183-linux.zip
 export JAVA_HOME=/home/josh/jdk1.8.0_60

android-studio/bin/studio.sh
 ( take the defaults, while this is going on proceed below )


mv Downloads/android-ndk-r10e-linux-x86_64.bin .
./android-studio/^C
chmod +x android-ndk-r10e-linux-x86_64.bin
./android-ndk-r10e-linux-x86_64.bin

mkdir StudioProjects
cp Downloads/wX3.7003.tar StudioProjects/
cd StudioProjects/
tar xf wX3.7003.tar





Migimport existing project
at first you'll need to setup API 23
once File -> Project Structure is not greyed out, open and select the Oracle JDK in $HOMErate from existing environment.



